  "prompt": "How do I write a very short summary of Hamlet?",
  "response": "Writing a very short summary of **\"Hamlet\"** involves distilling the play's complex plot and themes into a concise overview. Here\u2019s how you can approach it:\n\n1. **Identify the Main Plot**: Focus on the central storyline without delving into subplots.\n2. **Highlight Key Characters**: Mention the protagonist and any pivotal characters that drive the story.\n3. **Include the Central Conflict**: Outline the primary struggle or dilemma.\n4. **Mention the Setting (Optional)**: Briefly note where and when the story takes place, if relevant.\n5. **Keep It Concise**: Use clear and direct language to maintain brevity.\n\n### Example of a Very Short Summary:\n\n*\"Hamlet\" is a tragedy by William Shakespeare that follows Prince Hamlet of Denmark as he seeks revenge against his uncle, who has murdered Hamlet\u2019s father to seize the throne and marry his mother. The play explores themes of betrayal, madness, and the complexities of action.*\n\nThis summary captures the essential elements of the play while remaining brief. Adjust the length as needed based on your specific requirements.",
